The European Union changes the rules for obtaining visas
People should go to the service centres for the Visa applicants before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost the waiting time will be reduced.
As of January 10, 2011, the processing of visas at the embassy and consulates of the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants must present themselves to the service centres for the Visa applicants (CSA, according to) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The CSA staff take biometric information of the applicant, who will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will present some benefits for aspiring, among which refers to the following:
The total cost to treat the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment to get an appointment, another payment for the treatment of the visa and another for the mail service delivers the document.
They will make a single payment, which will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visa application (includes visas for temporary workers) and $390 for visas of traders and investors.
Persons wishing to renew their visas should not submit to an interview with the Representative Consular, they will only come to the nearest CSA, where they will have the documents and take their fingerprints.
Due to the fact that the biometric information will be made in the CSA, applicants who want a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section remain less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to consulates in Ciudad Juarez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra fee for service.
For more information on the new procedure to seek visas, visit the following page http:///mexico.usembassy.gov boletines/sp101201 _ Visa-FAQs.html
